<doc id="1133338" wikidata="Q288249" url="?curid=1133338" title="Tridiminished rhombicosidodecahedron">
<text>In geometry, the tridiminished rhombicosidodecahedron is one of the Johnson solids (). It can be constructed as a rhombicosidodecahedron with three pentagonal cupolae removed.

Related Johnson solids are:
* : diminished rhombicosidodecahedron with one cupola removed,
* : parabidiminished rhombicosidodecahedron with two opposing cupolae removed,
* : metabidiminished rhombicosidodecahedron with two non-opposing cupolae removed, and
* : gyrate bidiminished rhombicosidodecahedron with two non-opposing cupolae removed and one cupola rotated 36 degrees.

