<doc id="1133389" wikidata="Q5452071" url="?curid=1133389" title="Firin' Up">
<text>Firin&#x27; Up is the eighth studio album by American country rock band Pure Prairie League, released in 1980 (see 1980 in music) on their new label Casablanca. &quot;Let Me Love You Tonight&quot; is the band&#x27;s biggest pop hit, peaking at number 10 on the Billboard singles chart.

